<h1 style="margin-bottom:0px;">EC2 instances</h1><div class="f14 metric" style="color:#656668;display:flex;"><img src="/assets/images/calendar.png" style="height:12px;margin-top:auto;margin-bottom:auto;"><span class="updateDate">&nbsp; Updated on 26/06/2019</span> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; | &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <img src="/assets/images/updated.png" style="height:12px;margin-top:auto;margin-bottom:auto;"><span class="readTime">&nbsp; 4 minutes to read</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</div><br><div class="mw-parser-output"><p>Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud (Amazon EC2) instances are used to install and run CDF and the suite.&nbsp;
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Create_EC2_instances">Create EC2 instances</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/ECInOpsB&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=1" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: Create EC2 instances">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/ECInOpsB&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: Create EC2 instances">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p><b>Note</b>:
</p>
<ul><li>Follow the recommendations specified in  <a href="./itom/Operations_Bridge:2019.05/SizRecoOpsB" title="Operations Bridge:2019.05/SizRecoOpsB">Sizing considerations</a>.</li>
<li>Launch EC2 instances as masters and workers in each private subnet. In this example installation procedure, a total of 3 masters are needed, one for each private subnet.</li>
<li>Make sure to select <b>Eable Auto-assign Public IP</b> when creating a bastion. In addition, you must disable Source/Dest check on all masters and workers. To do so, right-click your EC2 instance, select <b>Network</b> &gt; <b>Change Source/Dest. Check</b>. Click <b>Yes, Disable</b> on the pop-up dialog.</li>
<li>Launch 1 or 2 <b>bastion</b>(t2.small size with 20GB) instances in each public subnet.</li>
<li>Create two key pairs, one for bastion instance and the other for other instances.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li></ul>
<p>To create an EC2 instance, follow these steps:
</p>
<ol><li>Open the Amazon EC2 console at&nbsp;<a target="1" rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="https://console.aws.amazon.com/ec2/">https://console.aws.amazon.com/ec2/</a>.</li>
<li>Choose&nbsp;<b>Launch Instance</b>.</li>
<li>In&nbsp;<b>Step 1: Choose an Amazon Machine Image (AMI) from AWS Marketplace</b>, search for <b>CentOS 7 (x86_64) - with Updates HVM</b>&nbsp;and choose&nbsp;<b>Select</b>.</li>
<li>In&nbsp;<b>Step 2: Choose an Instance Type</b>, select the instance type according to the sizing recommendations, for example, m4.2xlarge. Then, choose&nbsp;<b>Next: Configure Instance Details</b>.</li>
<li>In&nbsp;<b>Step 3: Configure Instance Details</b>, choose&nbsp;<b>Network</b>, and then choose the entry for your VPC created previously. It should look something like vpc-c01ea5ab | my_vpc.
<ol><li>Choose&nbsp;<b>Subnet</b>, and then choose a <b>Private Subnet</b> created previously.</li>
<li>Disable&nbsp;<b>Auto-assign Public IP</b>. <a onclick="javascript:loadingImage(this);" class="image"><img alt="OpsBridge2019.02EC23.jpg" src="/mediawiki/images/0/07/OpsBridge2019.02EC23.jpg" width="1313" height="778" data-file-width="1313" data-file-height="778"></a></li></ol></li>
<li>Choose&nbsp;<b>Next: Add Storage</b>.
<ol><li>Update the Root Volume according to the suite sizing recommendations.</li>
<li>Add <b>2 New Volume</b> of thin pool according to the suite sizing recommendations.  Refer to settings in the following example:   <a onclick="javascript:loadingImage(this);" class="image"><img alt="OpsBridge2019.02EC203.jpg" src="/mediawiki/images/8/8a/OpsBridge2019.02EC203.jpg" width="932" height="409" data-file-width="932" data-file-height="409"></a>
<ul><li><b>/dev/sda1</b> is root volume.</li>
<li><b>/dev/sdb</b> is for docker thinpool.</li>
<li><b>/dev/sdc</b> is for docker bootstrap.</li></ul></li></ol></li>
<li>Choose&nbsp;<b>Next: Add Tags</b>. Name your instance and choose&nbsp;<b>Next: Configure Security Group</b>.  <a onclick="javascript:loadingImage(this);" class="image"><img alt="OpsBridge2019.02EC25.jpg" src="/mediawiki/images/4/43/OpsBridge2019.02EC25.jpg" width="727" height="170" data-file-width="727" data-file-height="170"></a></li>
<li>In&nbsp;<b>Step 6: Configure Security Group</b>, review the contents of this page. Ensure that&nbsp;<b>Assign a security group</b>&nbsp;is set to&nbsp;<b>Create a new security group</b>. By default, the new security group's inbound rules only include SSH port 22. In this step, you can edit the inbound rules as shown in the example below, where only network traffice within the VPC is allowed. Later you can select <b>Existing Security Group</b> when launching other EC2 instances (excluding the bastion). <br> <a onclick="javascript:loadingImage(this);" class="image"><img alt="OpsBridge2019.02EC212.jpg" src="/mediawiki/images/1/1a/OpsBridge2019.02EC212.jpg" width="807" height="224" data-file-width="807" data-file-height="224"></a><br></li></ol>
<a class="buttonfullscr" onclick="javascript:loadingTableButton(this);"><button class="flscrbtn"><i class="material-icons flscricn">open_in_new</i><div style="margin: auto 5px;">View Fullscreen</div></button></a><table>

