</td></tr></tbody></table>
<p><br>
</p>
<dl><dd>9. Replace <b>Source'<i> with your </i></b><i>VPC CIDR<b>. <br><br></b></i><b>Note</b>: You can edit this security group with more strict rules later. For details, see <a href="./itom/SMAX:2019.02/EnableFirewallOnNode" title="SMAX:2019.02/EnableFirewallOnNode"> Ports List</a><br><br></dd>
<dd>10. Click&nbsp;<b>Review and Launch</b>.<br></dd>
<dd>11. Select a <b>Key Pair</b> or create a new one.  AWS EC2 instances could be ssh login only by this private key. <br></dd>
<dd>12. Choose&nbsp;<b>Launch</b>.<br><br><b>Note</b>: For more information about creating Amazon EC2, see <a target="1" rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="https://docs.aws.amazon.com/efs/latest/ug/gs-step-one-create-ec2-resources.html">https://docs.aws.amazon.com/efs/latest/ug/gs-step-one-create-ec2-resources.html</a>.&nbsp;<br><br>In order for the Master and Worker nodes to communicate with each other, the instances will need to be modified by disabling the Source/Destination Check. <br><br></dd></dl>
<ol><li>Select one of the instances created to install the suite and from the Action button select Networking and Change Source/Dest. Check. <br> <a onclick="javascript:loadingImage(this);" class="image"><img alt="OpsBridge2019.02EC219.jpg" src="/mediawiki/images/6/60/OpsBridge2019.02EC219.jpg" width="678" height="363" data-file-width="678" data-file-height="363"></a> <br></li>
<li>Confirm Disabling. <br> <a onclick="javascript:loadingImage(this);" class="image"><img alt="OpsBridge2019.02EC220.jpg" src="/mediawiki/images/3/3b/OpsBridge2019.02EC220.jpg" width="820" height="318" data-file-width="820" data-file-height="318"></a></li>
<li>Repeat steps 1-3 on the other instances that were created.</li></ol>
<p><br>
</p>
